# <type>(<scope>): <subject>
# Examples: feat(backend), fix(auth), test(e2e), docs(readme), chore(deps)
#
# ─── Types ────────────────────────────────────────────────
# feat:     New feature
# fix:      Bug fix
# docs:     Documentation changes
# style:    Formatting, missing semi colons, etc; no code change
# refactor: Refactoring production code
# test:     Adding missing tests, refactoring tests; no production code change
# chore:    Build tasks, package manager configs, etc; no production code change
#
# ─── Subject Rules ────────────────────────────────────────
# - Use imperative mood ("add", "change", not "added", "changed")
# - Max 50 characters
# - No period at the end
#
# ─── Body (Optional) ──────────────────────────────────────
# Explain the *why* and *how* of the changes, not the *what*.
# Max 72 characters per line.
#
# ─── Footer (Optional) ────────────────────────────────────
# Reference issues, breakages, etc.
# Example: Closes #123
